HEADWORD: Leucadendron
<hw>Leu`ca*den"dron</hw>
<pr>(l⟦umac⟧`k⟦adot⟧*d⟦ecr⟧n"dr⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>leyko`s</grk> white + <grk>de`ndron</grk> tree.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of evergreen shrubs from the Cape of Good
Hope, having handsome foliage. <spn>Leucadendron argenteum</spn> is the
<stype>silverboom</stype> of the colonists.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

